03/11/2003
PRESPA, Macedonia -- The fire fighting departments of Albania, Greece and Macedonia signed an agreement Friday (31 October) to co-operate in protecting Prespa Lake.
The border region is known for its natural beauty and biodiversity.
Experts from the three countries focused on a common forest firefighting plan, but also reviewed other areas of co-operation.
The meeting was sponsored by the Greek Foreign Ministry's International Development Co-operation Agency.
(MIA, MPA - 31/10/03)
